What it Does
Adds more names to the blocklist as well as a good-deeds verification to ensure they are truly an "evil" person before admitting them

What it Demonstrates
Logical operators basics (or, and)
Compounded booleans in evil_status =="Yes" and gooddeeds_status < 4

What to Improve on
Long or chain in both the blocked list as well as the long price list for menu items

Code

print("Hello, welcome to Zach's coffee shop!")

Menu = "\nBlack Coffee\nMacchiato\nLatte\nEspresso\nCappuccino\nFrappuccino\n"

CustomerName = input("What is your name?\n" )

if CustomerName == "Iron Man" or  CustomerName == "Thor" or CustomerName == "Loki":
  evil_status = input("Are you evil " + CustomerName + "?\n")
  gooddeeds_status = int(input("How many good deeds have you done today?\n"))
  if evil_status == "Yes" and gooddeeds_status < 4 :
    print("Sorry, you're not welcome here.")
    exit()
  else:
    print("\nSorry about that " + CustomerName + ", thank you so much for coming in today! Here is our menu.\n" + Menu)
else:
  print("\nHello " + CustomerName + ", thank you so much for coming in today! Here is our menu.\n" + Menu)
  
order = input("What can I get started for you?\n")

if order == "Frappuccino":
  price = 8
  whipped_cream_status = input("Would you like to add whipped cream for an extra $2?")
  if whipped_cream_status == "Yes":
    price = 10
  else:
    price = 8
elif order == "Black Coffee":
  price = 3
elif order == "Espresso":
  price = 2
elif order == "Macchiato":
  price = 5
elif order == "Cappuccino":
  price = 4
elif order == "Latte":
  price = 5
else:
  print("Sorry, we can't make that here.")
  price = 0

print("\nYou got it " + CustomerName + ". ")

numberordered = input("How many would you like?\n")
total = price * int(numberordered)

print("Your total is: $" + str(total) + "\n")

print("You got it. I will have your " + numberordered + " " + order + " right out in a few minutes!")
